 ✅ 1) Introduction to CSS3

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and layout HTML elements.

Syntax:
selector {
  property: value;
}

Example:
p {
  color: red;
  font-size: 16px;
}

p → selector
color, font-size → properties
red, 16px → values

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 2) Ways to Apply CSS (Interview Favorite ⭐⭐)

1️⃣ Inline CSS (inside element)
<h1 style="color: blue;">Hello</h1>
✅ Quick but not recommended

2️⃣ Internal CSS (inside <style>)
<style>
 h1 { color: green; }
</style>
✅ Good for small pages

3️⃣ External CSS (best practice ⭐)
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
✅ Best for real projects
✅ Reusable + clean


Priority order:

Inline CSS
Internal CSS
External CSS

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 3) CSS Selectors (Most Important ⭐⭐)

Selectors choose which elements to style.

Basic Selectors:

Element selector
p { color: red; }

Class selector (most used ⭐)
.box { background: yellow; }

ID selector (unique)
#main { padding: 20px; }

Group selector
h1, h2, p { font-family: Arial; }

Universal selector
 * {}

📌 Interview must know:
ID should be unique, class can be reused.

