✅ 5) Box Model Basics (Most Important ⭐⭐)

Every HTML element is treated as a box made of:
Content
Padding
Border
Margin

Example:
div {
 width: 200px;
 padding: 20px;
 border: 2px solid black;
 margin: 10px;
}

Quick meaning:

Content = actual text/image area
Padding = space inside border
Border = outline
Margin = space outside element

📌 Interview line:
Box model defines spacing and size of elements using content, padding, border and margin.

