 ✅ 7) Layout with CSS (Display, Position, Float) ⭐⭐

✅ Display

Most common display types:

block :
Takes full width
Examples: div, p, h1

inline :
Takes only required space
Examples: span, a

inline-block :
Inline but can set width/height

span {
 display: inline-block;
 width: 100px;
}

(🔥 MMI). Explain position property.

Answer:

Position	Meaning
static		default
relative	relative to itself
absolute	relative to nearest positioned parent
fixed		relative to viewport
sticky		mix of relative + fixed

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 8) Flexbox Layout (Most Important ⭐⭐⭐)

Flexbox is a CSS layout model used to arrange elements in a row or column.
It is best for one-dimensional layouts.

Flexbox is used to:
	Align items horizontally or vertically
	Center elements easily
	Create navbars, cards, rows


.container {
  display: flex;
}

🔥 MMI). Explain flex-direction.

Answer:

flex-direction: row;
flex-direction: column;

(🔥 MMI). Explain justify-content.

Answer:

justify-content: center;
justify-content: space-between;
justify-content: space-around;

Aligns items along main axis.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ✅ 9) CSS Grid Layout (Most Important ⭐⭐⭐)

CSS Grid is a layout system used to create rows and columns.
It is best for two-dimensional layouts.

Grid is used to:
	Create full page layouts
	Control both rows and columns

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 ✅ 9) Responsive Web Design (Most Important ⭐⭐⭐)

Responsive design means:
Website adjusts automatically to mobile, tablet, desktop.

Responsive design makes web pages adapt to different screen sizes.
Achieved using:
	Flexible layouts
	Media queries

Media Queries :
Used to apply CSS based on screen size.
CSS rule to apply styles based on screen width/device.

@media (max-width: 768px) {
 body { background: red; }
}
👉 Screen ≤ 768px → CSS applies

✅ Breakpoints (Most common)

Breakpoints are screen widths where layout changes.

Typical breakpoints:

576px (mobile)
768px (tablet)
992px (laptop)
1200px (desktop)



